ban land use, the right to the city and the value of social connection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunity gardensxSocial aspects. 0aCommunity gardenszScotlandzGlasgow. 0aCommunity gardens. 0aUrban agriculturezScotlandzGlasgow. 0aUrban renewal. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Geography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831111967940 cprintz978152922069840uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529220711?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529220711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529220711/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles